        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 7:26PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 726 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southwest of Red Level, or 13 miles southeast of Evergreen,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
River Falls, Red Level, Heath, and Gantt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
